<h1 id="section">Services</h1>

<div>

I host a range of services from my home server and various servers around the interweb. The current and historical statuses of all my services are displayed [here](https://status.vale.rocks). Some	of the stuff I host includes:

<div id="services">
<article>
    <h2>Fediverse</h2>
    <a href="https://fedi.vale.rocks">Website</a>
    <p>Akkoma instance for accessing the fediverse.</p>
    <details>
        <summary>Read More</summary>
        I host my own personal Fediverse instance using <a href="https://akkoma.social">Akkoma</a>, which allows me to easily federate with a range of other Activity Pub based
        <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fediverse">fediverse</a> platforms. The instance itself is invite only, but I'm available to follow as
        <a href="https://fedi.vale.rocks/vale">@vale@fedi.vale.rocks</a>.
    </details>
</article>

<article>
    <h2>Jellyfin</h2>
    <a href="https://jellyfin.vale.rocks">Website</a>
    <p>Free and open source media server.</p>
    <details>
        <summary>Read More</summary>
        I host my media library containing a wide assortment of films, books, audiobooks, and shows for my viewing pleasure. The instance is invite only and not accepting sign-ups. 
    </details>
</article>

<article>
    <h2>AutoMod</h2>
    <a href="https://automod.vale.rocks">Website</a>
    <p>Moderation bot for <a href="https://revolt.chat">Revolt</a>.</p>
    <details>
        <summary>Read More</summary>
        Full scale moderation bot servicing in excess of 4,000 servers and tens of thousands of users. Hosted on a Hetzner VPS.
    </details>
</article>

